Figure 6 summarizes the binding energies with respect to alloy composition. The fitted line indicates that binding energies are not linear as a function of alloy composition (i.e. Vegard’s law is invalid in this case). The deviation from linearity of the binding energies of Si1−xGex (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
