				\begin{document}$${E}_{b}^{SiGe}=(1-x){E}_{b}^{Si}+x{E}_{b}^{Ge}+x(1-x)\theta $$\end{document}EbSiGe=(1−x)EbSi+xEbGe+x(1−x)θWhere θ is called the bowing parameter and is calculated to be −2.0 eV. Although the trend is very similar, this bowing parameter is considerably higher as compared to the one calculated in previous work5. This is due to the more substantial SQS cells (32 atom SQS as compared to 16 atom SQS in ref.5) and the more Si1−xGex compositions used here that allow far more E-centre configurations to be considered.Figure 6
